headline: Ross Stores (ROST) Stock Is Up, What You Need To Know
summary: Shares of off-price retail company Ross Stores (NASDAQ:ROST) jumped 4.2% in the afternoon session after the company announced it completed its fiscal 2025 store expansion with 40 new locations, and Citigroup raised its price target on the stock.

headline: 1 Safe-and-Steady Stock Worth Investigating and 2 We Brush Off
summary: Stability is great, but low-volatility stocks may struggle to deliver market-beating returns over time as they sometimes underperform during bull markets.
